    "rich_text_Xj6Lqf": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_Nfdnfj": {
          "type": "heading",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "heading": "<h4>Welcome to XX-XY Athletics!<br/></h4>",
            "heading_size": "medium",
            "heading_padding_top": 0,
            "padding_bottom": 0
          }
        },
        "text_3XRk3M": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Jennifer Sey spent the better part of her adult and professional life working for a very famous jeans brand that will remain nameless here. She then got herself cancelled after more than 2 decades at the company because she said “hey maybe public schools should be open [during covid] just like the private schools!” The audacity. ​</p><p>​</p><p>So that was that. No more [insert famous jeans brand] CEO job for her. So, she decided to make her own opportunity. What could be more American than that? ​</p><p>​</p><p>Former Leftie, currently unaffiliated atheist, Jennifer is proud to work alongside a rag tag group of cancelled, ousted and otherwise self-described misfits who all believe in one thing: freedom. Some are religious. Some are not. Some are big mouths. Some are not. Some are life-long conservatives. Some are not. But here’s the thing – everyone gets along, is committed to not being easily offended (or ever offended) and everyone on this team wants to make great stuff that you – dear fan -- will be proud to wear. ​</p><p>​</p><p>Help us prove the parallel economy isn’t just bad beer, mediocre chocolate and weird apps no one wants. The future of the parallel – or freedom – economy is world class product made for people with discriminating tastes and a penchant for liberty. ​</p><p>​</p>"
          }
        },
